data.text:
Do you remember whose voice was in The Rescuers and who starred in the live-action classic Escape to Witch Mountain?

Hooterville was populated by some of the friendliest, funniest and goofiest actors on TV. It’s no wonder they all appeared in a Disney movie at one point or another. A few actors with famous voices even starred in multiple animated classics.

Everyone from the Douglases (Eddie Albert and Eva Gabor) to the county agent (Alvy Moore) to the Monroe “brothers” (Sid Melton and Mary Grace Canfield) to the general store proprietor (Frank Cady) starred in animated and live-action Disney films from the Sixties, Seventies and Eighties.

Do you remember which Green Acres cast members were in these movies?

Who starred in Disney classic The Rescuers?

Eddie Albert

Eva Gabor

Tom Lester

Who voiced a character in Disney’s take on Robin Hood?

Pat Buttram

Frank Cady

Alvy Moore

Who appeared in the live-action drama Escape to Witch Mountain?

Mary Grace Canfield

Sid Melton

Eddie Albert

Who appeared in the Love Bug sequel Herbie Rides Again?

Eva Gabor

Alvy Moore

Frank Cady

Who was one of many famous TV voices in The Fox and the Hound?

Eddie Albert

Tom Lester

Pat Buttram

Who appeared in the egg-stravagant movie The Million Dollar Duck?

Sid Melton

Frank Cady

Hank Patterson

Who starred in the toe-tappin’ animated classic The Aristocats?

Eva Gabor

Barbara Pepper

Alvy Moore

Who appeared with this star-studded cast in Pollyanna?

Sid Melton

Frank Cady

Mary Grace Canfield

Who starred in the drama Miracle of the White Stallions?

Eddie Albert

Eleanor Audley

Pat Buttram

Benji isn’t technically a Disney movie, but it may as well be. Which Green Acres actor appears in this canine classic?

Eva Gabor

Tom Lester

Frank Cady
